# Fixture FM6: @base and BASE directives replace (not accumulate) the active
# base IRI. SPARQL-style BASE must be supported in Turtle 1.1.
#
# Hypothesis:
#   (a) A parser that ignores the SPARQL-style `BASE` keyword will resolve
#       `<rel>` against `<http://example/a/>` instead of `<http://example/b/>`.
#   (b) A parser that accumulates bases will also produce the wrong IRI.
#
# Expected: <rel> resolves to <http://example/b/rel>.
#   Triple: <http://example/b/rel> <http://example/b/p> <http://example/b/o> .
#
# Divergence signal: ObjectMismatch or FactOnlyIn if the base is wrong.
#
# Spec: Turtle §2.2 — "The base URI is updated for each occurrence."
# SPARQL-style BASE added in RDF 1.1 Turtle. Note: per Turtle §6.5, the
# SPARQL-style `BASE <iri>` production has no trailing `.` (unlike the
# `@base <iri> .` form); this fixture therefore omits the dot after the
# SPARQL-style directive so the grammar claim stays on "replacement, not
# accumulation" rather than accidentally asserting terminator tolerance.

@base <http://example/a/> .
BASE <http://example/b/>
<rel> <p> <o> .
